    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=849#comment-17597' data-commentid="17597" data-postid="849" data-belowelement="comment-17597" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-17598" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Karen</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=849#comment-17598"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-01T11:42:11-04:00">Saturday, May 1, 2010 at 11:42 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi, Molly&#8230;</p>
<p>Picked up your book last weekend and finally got to start it Thursday. </p>
<p>Your description of the Maine bed-and-breakfast stopped me cold; I had to call my spouse and read him the paragraphs. Seeing one of my fondest memories in print, without having written it, was startling and thrilling.</p>
<p>For several years, a trip to Jerry and Tony&#39;s inn was the highlight of our winter. &#39;Our&#39; room (the top floor with the outside entrance) was above the kitchen. We&#39;d wake each morning to the most amazing aromas wafting through the eaves, and play guessing games about what  awaited us in the sunroom. No matter the day&#39;s plans, we never missed tea and the blissful torment of choosing a dessert from the half-dozen options. </p>
<p>Jerry and Tony&#39;s food changed something in both of us. My vegetable-hating husband tried (and grudgingly admitted liking) roasted Brussels sprouts. The two kinds of pate served at tea were a revelation, and every scone I&#39;ve had since then has disappointed. At their table, we experienced flavors, textures and scents  unimaginable before.</p>
<p>Thank you for rekindling those memories, and for a book filled with humor, insight and deliciousness.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=849#comment-17598' data-commentid="17598" data-postid="849" data-belowelement="comment-17598" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Karen" aria-label='Reply to Karen'>Reply</a>    </div>
